abstract: President Donald Trump wants to work with North Korea to help it develop its economy, but the United States does not want to see a resumption of "ill-advised behavior" by Pyongyang, a senior State Department official said on Thursday.
snippet: President Donald Trump wants to work with North Korea to help it develop its economy, but the United States does not want to see a resumption of "ill-advised behavior" by Pyongyang, a senior State Department official said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump wants to work with North Korea to help it develop its economy, but the United States does not want to see a resumption of "ill-advised behavior" by Pyongyang, a senior State Department official said on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. Does Not Want to See 'Ill-Advised Behavior' by North Korea: Official
headline_print_headline: U.S. Does Not Want to See 'Ill-Advised Behavior' by North Korea: Official

abstract: The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
snippet: The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Confirms John Sullivan as Next U.S. Ambassador to Russia
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Confirms John Sullivan as Next U.S. Ambassador to Russia

abstract: The reality show’s sexual misconduct saga proved the consequences of not doing the right thing from the beginning.
snippet: The reality show’s sexual misconduct saga proved the consequences of not doing the right thing from the beginning.
lead_paragraph: Is “Survivor” real life or is it a show? The CBS reality competition, in which contestants vote one another off an island week by week as they fight for a million dollars, likes to see itself as both: a snow-globe version of the world, a “social experiment,” as the producer Mark Burnett calls it, in which human nature plays out under pressure and on camera.

abstract: As the House takes another step toward impeaching President Trump, concern is increasing that trying to remove a president will become a more common partisan tool.
snippet: As the House takes another step toward impeaching President Trump, concern is increasing that trying to remove a president will become a more common partisan tool.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was a powerful congressional weapon deployed in only the most extreme cases, so explosive that lawmakers feared the wider damage it could do if used for the wrong reasons. Today, the filibuster is an everyday part of Senate business, standard operating procedure in a polarized world where the once rare has become commonplace.

abstract: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
snippet: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
lead_paragraph: In this week’s roundup of student comments on our writing prompts, we asked young people to weigh in on whether the United States owes reparations to the descendants of slaves, tell us what they wished they could learn in school, and reflect on their identities.

abstract: The Senate on Thursday confirmed Dr. Stephen Hahn to lead the Food and Drug Administration despite concerns about how he will confront the growing problem of underage vaping.
snippet: The Senate on Thursday confirmed Dr. Stephen Hahn to lead the Food and Drug Administration despite concerns about how he will confront the growing problem of underage vaping.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Thursday confirmed Dr. Stephen Hahn to lead the Food and Drug Administration despite concerns about how he will confront the growing problem of underage vaping.
headline_main: Senate OKs Trump's FDA Nominee Despite Unclear Vaping Agenda
headline_print_headline: Senate OKs Trump's FDA Nominee Despite Unclear Vaping Agenda

abstract: The Food and Drug Administration has been without a permanent commissioner since April, when Dr. Scott Gottlieb resigned.
snippet: The Food and Drug Administration has been without a permanent commissioner since April, when Dr. Scott Gottlieb resigned.
lead_paragraph: The Senate voted 72 to 18 to confirm Dr. Stephen Hahn as commissioner of the Food and Drug Administration, as the agency faces pressure to reduce teenage vaping and weighs competing interests on a long-delayed proposal to ban flavored e-cigarettes.

abstract: Mass killings of more than a million Armenians by Ottoman Turks a century ago were genocide, the Senate declared Thursday in a vote that prompted angry denunciations by Turkey and accusations that the U.S. was undermining its relations with a key NATO ally.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mass killings of more than a million Armenians by Ottoman Turks a century ago were genocide, the Senate declared Thursday in a vote that prompted angry denunciations by Turkey and accusations that the U.S. was undermining its relations with a key NATO ally.
headline_main: Senate Backs Measure Affirming Century-Old Armenian Genocide
